Description:
If you need to update multiple entities at once, you need to do it like this at the moment:

{code}
Query myQuery = Query.select().where("firstColumn = ?", firstValue);
MyEntity[] myEntities = ao.find(MyEntity.class, myQuery);
for (MyEntity myEntity : myEntities) {
    myEntity.setSecondColumn(secondValue);
    myEntity.save();
}
{code}

This results in lots of the following SQL statements:
{code}
UPDATE myEntity
SET secondColumn = "secondValue"
WHERE ID = x
{code}

For every single entity that needs to be updated.

This could be improved with something like this (just my suggestion, not sure whether this is possible):

{code}
Query myQuery = Query.select().where("firstColumn = ?", firstValue);
ao.update(MyEntity.class, myQuery, "secondColumn", "secondValue");
{code}

At the end, the following statement should be executed:

{code}
UPDATE myEntity
SET secondColumn = "secondValue"
WHERE firstColumn = "firstValue"
{code}

I know it's not as easy as it looks like, but it would be a huge improvement if you need to update multiple entities at once.

